ms is 59 km s$^{-1}$. Because lower mass compact objects,\nlike NSs, are expected to receive larger natal kicks than higher mass BHs, this\nmay explain why asymmetric NSBH systems merge more frequently than asymmetric\nBBH systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 10 Mar 2023 16:59:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-13"}
